{title: Freight Train Boogie}
{artist: Willie Nelson}
{composer: Written by Doc Watson}

[C]Casey Jones he was a mighty man
But now he's resting in the promised land
The kind of music he could understand
Was an eight wheel driver under his command
He made the [F]freight train boogie all the [C]time
He made the [G7]freight train boogie as he rolled down the [C]line
[C]When the fireman started ringing the bell
Everybody hung around to tell
Casey Jones was a coming to town
On a six eight wheeler that was flat on the ground
Repeat #2,1,2,3,2